	<dd><a name="comment_1049" ></a>
	<p><em><strong>smiggins</strong> replies:</em> No, nothing racist about asserting it per se.</p> <p>The Tories' "it's not racist..." line is a time-honoured<br />political trick of objecting to something that no-one is actually suggesting.  Of course it isn't actually racist to put limits on immigration, it would only be racist if the immigration rules were applied differently to different races.</p> <p>Since we know full well what the Tories would actually do in power, i.e. break European immigration law for a start, it's probably fair enough to assert that they would also come up with a policy which is objectively racist in its implementation.</p>
	<small>
